com.gensym.core
Class ModifiableBeanInfo

Direct Known Subclasses:
ModifiableBeanInfo
public abstract class ModifiableBeanInfo
extends SimpleBeanInfo

ModifiableBeanInfo is a really useful hack that allows one to override the default behavior of Introspector.getBeanInfo(). It is not obvious to the author why Javasoft did not make the Introspector a little more open. The implementation of this class seems to be a little bit hackish, but is hoped that it is at least has good hygiene.

It provides four protected methods to be overridden by subclasses. getBeanClass() informs the parent class of what bean is being introspected. The other three are methods that allow the subclasses to inspect and modify FeatureDescriptors that are created by the default Introspector getBeanInfo.
